79.2	Sangria	Sangria	Sangria (Spanish: Sangr√≠a) is a wine punch typical of Argentina, Spain and Portugal. It normally consists of wine, chopped fruit, a sweetener, and a small amount of added brandy. In the case of fruits, they are chopped or sliced such as orange, lemon, lime, apple, peach, melon, berries, pineapple, grape and mango. A sweetener such as honey, sugar, simple syrup, orange juice is added. Instead of brandy, other liquids such as Seltzer, Sprite or 7 Up may be added.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Dos_Jarras_de_Sangr%C3%ADa-2009.jpg/220px-Dos_Jarras_de_Sangr%C3%ADa-2009.jpg
